Architecture plan for issues #37-#45

Project shape
- Product: Rust Learning Manual, a Vite/React/Tailwind MDX learning site with an Express `/run` proxy for runnable Rust snippets.
- Frontend: `apps/web`.
  - Manual content lives in `apps/web/src/content/*.mdx`.
  - Section registration and navigation data live in `apps/web/src/content/manual.ts`.
  - Shared MDX components are wired through `apps/web/src/content/mdxComponents.tsx`.
  - Reusable presentation components live under `apps/web/src/components/content`.
  - Runnable playground UI lives under `apps/web/src/components/playground`.
- Backend: `apps/api`.
  - Keep the existing `/run` proxy and rate-limited validation behavior unchanged unless a later content issue exposes an actual compatibility problem.
  - Content issues should call the existing frontend run client through `RunnableSnippet`; the browser should not call the Rust Playground directly.

Issue sequencing
- #37-#40 deepen the four existing sections:
  - `getting-started.mdx`
  - `ownership.mdx`
  - `types.mdx`
  - `errors.mdx`
- #41-#45 add new sections:
  - `structs-traits.mdx`
  - `collections-iterators.mdx`
  - `modules-crates.mdx`
  - `lifetimes.mdx`
  - `testing.mdx`
- Each new section must be imported and registered in `manual.ts` with stable `id`, `path`, metadata, heading extraction source, and navigation order.
- #44 should build conceptually on the expanded Ownership section, but implementation remains isolated to a new MDX file plus navigation registration.

Content conventions
- Use MDX metadata exports with `label`, `title`, and `description`.
- Prefer `RunnableSnippet` for examples that should execute in the inline playground.
- Keep non-runnable examples in fenced Rust code blocks so `CodeBlock` provides copy controls.
- Use `Callout` for notes, tips, warnings, and conceptual guardrails instead of one-off markup.
- Keep examples beginner-oriented, compile-ready, and small enough for the existing `/run` size caps.
- Avoid introducing persistence, uploads, auth flows, or new backend routes for these content-only issues.

Validation expectations
- For content-only changes, run at least typecheck/build; run frontend tests or E2E when changing component usage patterns or runnable snippet behavior.
- When adding a section, verify the sidebar navigation and in-page table of contents show the new headings.
